250 g Ground Beef
2 unit Artisan Bun
113 g Baby Tomatoes
113 g Spring Mix
56 g Kale, chopped
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, grated
4 tbsp Caesar Dressing
3 tbsp Sour Cream
2 tsp Hot Sauce
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
½ tbsp Oil*
0.38 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
28 g Croutons

Before starting, preset the broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.Heat Guide for Step 4: 1 tsp (2 tsp) mild, 2 tsp (4 tsp) medium, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) spicy and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) extra-spicy! Remove any stems from kale and roughly chop.Halve tomatoes.

Add beef, garlic puree and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt to a medium bowl. Season with pepper, then combine. Form mixture into two 4-inch-wide patties (4 patties for 4 ppl).

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then patties. Pan-fry until cooked through, 4-5 min per side.** \When patties are almost done, top with half the mozzarella, then cover until melted.

While patties cook, halve buns. Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Sprinkle remaining mozzarella over buns. Broil in the middle of the oven until buns are golden-brown and mozzarella is melted, 1-2 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)While mozzarella melts, combine sour cream and 2 tsp (4 tsp) hot sauce in a small bowl. (NOTE: Reference heat guide.) Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Add Caesar dressing, tomatoes, croutons, kale and three-quarters of the spring mix to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Spread spicy crema over bottom buns, then stack with remaining spring mix and chorizo patties. Close with top buns. Divide beefqueso burgers and salad between plates. Sprinkle Parmesan over salad.